{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/bit-01/bit_01/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"085f0a7d-dd59-5b6c-9a50-05144e40f017","html":"<h1>TLDR</h1>\n<p>Use <strong><a href=\"https://www.gitignore.io\">.gitignore.io</a></strong> and consider adding an alias to your terminal to quickly add a .gitignore to any project missing one.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\"><span class=\"token builtin class-name\">alias</span> <span class=\"token assign-left variable\">gitignore</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">'curl https://www.gitignore.io/api/vim,emacs,python,pycharm,sublimetext,visualstudio,visualstudiocode,data > .gitignore'</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Add a minimal <strong>setup.py</strong> to the root of your project, and use the following command to install it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">pip <span class=\"token function\">install</span> -e <span class=\"token builtin class-name\">.</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>consider using **<a href=\"https://github.com/audreyr/cookiecutter\">cookiecutter</a></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2019-02-10T00:00:00.000Z","title":"Minimal Project Structure","description":"How to setup a data science project in python.","path":"journey","twitter_cover":null,"cover":{"id":"aaad77c8-ccf4-5197-bb36-3d99fe051ce4","absolutePath":"/mnt/c/personal/ww/waylonwalkerv2/src/pages/blog/bit-01/verstappen-photography-532656-unsplash.jpg","childImageSharp":{"id":"e68f1dcc-ea74-5b66-b71f-e57712b724b2","fixed":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","width":1000,"height":420,"src":"/static/65bd089e358383c3792fd65060c146b6/9cf42/verstappen-photography-532656-unsplash.jpg","srcSet":"/static/65bd089e358383c3792fd65060c146b6/9cf42/verstappen-photography-532656-unsplash.jpg 1x,\n/static/65bd089e358383c3792fd65